To start an angular project
    - ng new (project-name)
    -cd into the project, the ng serve

To generate a new component | service | pipe | etc
    - ng g c 
    - ng g s
    - ng g p
    - ng g etc..

    You can also generate it with test run by adding --dry-run

    Angular:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    directives: <app-name></app-name> html code
    What is the first directive given when you create a new component? <app-root></app-root>

    What is a directive? Where there is a directive, at runtime it will inject the corresponding html fragment,
        then the css will style that html, and the ts file will control it (logic/dom/manipulation) the html/css

    A directive ALWAYS belongs to a component
        like app-root belongs to app.component
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ 

component: @component in a ts file!
@component requires 3 things!
    - selector aka directive name like app-root which become <app-root></app-root>
    - Template like HTML
 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 Data-binding {{}} Angular expression

TS file -> HTML files 

 1 way data binding
 from what to what? well we're only talking about components and components only have 3 things: html,css, ts
    -Data binding means sharing the same data between them

mini angular assignment: create an agular project, generate 2 components and use angular {{}} 
                to print 2 seperate values to the html files
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What are structural directives
    There are 3 structural directives mainly flow control
    - *ngFor
    - *ngIf
    - *ngSwitch
